FcConfigEnableHome(3)                                                                                                                                                                FcConfigEnableHome(3)

NAME
       FcConfigEnableHome - controls use of the home directory.

SYNOPSIS
       #include <fontconfig/fontconfig.h>

       FcBool FcConfigEnableHome (FcBool enable);

DESCRIPTION
       If enable is FcTrue, then Fontconfig will use various files which are specified relative to the user's home directory (using the ~ notation in the configuration). When enable is FcFalse, then all
       use of the home directory in these contexts will be disabled. The previous setting of the value is returned.

